1
00:00:00,700 --> 00:00:02,590
Previously on Fairy Tail:

2
00:00:02,590 --> 00:00:06,300
Hey Natsu, don't you think our guild 
has a whole lot of special events?

3
00:00:06,300 --> 00:00:09,320
Yeah... There's the that 
big parade, the Fantasia...

4
00:00:09,320 --> 00:00:10,920
Then there's the hanami bingo tournament...

5
00:00:10,920 --> 00:00:13,530
And don't forget about the 
Miss Fairy Tail contest!

6
00:00:13,530 --> 00:00:16,370
Wait, did you win that, Lucy?

7
00:00:16,370 --> 00:00:20,040
Please don't ask me that... Seriously.

8
00:02:04,230 --> 00:02:06,530
So cool!

9
00:02:06,530 --> 00:02:09,150
It's that time of year again! 
This grand event is here!

10
00:02:09,150 --> 00:02:15,530
Fairy Tail's traditional All-Wizards 
Mandatory Participation 24 Hours Road Race!

11
00:02:15,530 --> 00:02:20,440
And I, Jason, from the Weekly Sorcerer, 
will be doing the play-by-play!

12
00:02:20,440 --> 00:02:25,490
I'll be giving you the cool 
scoop on this hot event!

13
00:02:27,400 --> 00:02:30,640
24-Hour Endurance Road Race!

14
00:02:33,100 --> 00:02:34,330
Here he is!

15
00:02:34,330 --> 00:02:37,820
The unbeatable titleholder 
for this road race, Jet!

16
00:02:37,820 --> 00:02:42,150
Rumors say he's compensating for 
being mostly useless on quests!

17
00:02:42,150 --> 00:02:42,840
Hey!

18
00:02:42,840 --> 00:02:44,980
Just rumors, man!

19
00:02:44,980 --> 00:02:48,510
Damn that Jet... He thinks this year's 
gonna be a walk in the park again.

20
00:02:48,510 --> 00:02:51,330
Oh yeah? I wouldn't be so sure of that.

21
00:02:51,330 --> 00:02:53,300
Victory is mine!

22
00:02:53,300 --> 00:02:57,480
Nobody who says "victory is 
mine" ever actually wins.

23
00:02:57,480 --> 00:02:59,930
I gots me a super-secret weapon.

24
00:02:59,930 --> 00:03:03,310
A secret weapon? You're such a little kid.

25
00:03:07,600 --> 00:03:09,540
All right, let's do this!

26
00:03:09,540 --> 00:03:12,080
You're drinking? Right 
before we start the run?

27
00:03:12,080 --> 00:03:14,830
I can't run without fuel, right?

28
00:03:14,830 --> 00:03:16,430
I figured you'd say 
something like that, Cana.

29
00:03:16,430 --> 00:03:18,980
Everyone's really revved up, though.

30
00:03:18,980 --> 00:03:21,830
No one wants to face the 
punishment, after all.

31
00:03:21,830 --> 00:03:24,530
Last year was horrible...

32
00:03:25,230 --> 00:03:26,850
What punishment?

33
00:03:26,850 --> 00:03:28,970
Quiet, everyone!

34
00:03:28,970 --> 00:03:31,260
All members of Fairy Tail!

35
00:03:31,260 --> 00:03:35,450
A wizard is one with both 
strength of mind and body!

36
00:03:35,450 --> 00:03:39,030
I wish for you to utilize those powers 
to the utmost in today's competition!

37
00:03:39,030 --> 00:03:41,210
Do we really need smarts for this?

38
00:03:41,210 --> 00:03:44,170
Seems pretty much just 
physical endurance to me.

39
00:03:44,170 --> 00:03:46,120
The rules are simple!

40
00:03:46,120 --> 00:03:48,740
You will run as fast as you 
can from the start line,

41
00:03:48,740 --> 00:03:52,250
then here along the appointed 
course, heading for Mt. Ivor!

42
00:03:52,250 --> 00:03:56,690
This year, I have left Wyvern 
scales at the top of Mt. Ivor!

43
00:03:56,980 --> 00:04:02,440
You will take one of those scales, 
and return here within 24 hours!

44
00:04:02,440 --> 00:04:04,260
I won't accept any dropouts.

45
00:04:04,260 --> 00:04:07,620
If you are a Fairy Tail Wizard, 
then you will run the distance,

46
00:04:07,620 --> 00:04:10,600
all the way to your next job tomorrow!

47
00:04:10,600 --> 00:04:16,150
Furthermore, I am imposing a new regulation 
this year at the urging of many...

48
00:04:16,150 --> 00:04:18,850
Flying magic is forbidden!

49
00:04:20,490 --> 00:04:23,480
Other than that, any type 
of magic is allowed!

50
00:04:23,480 --> 00:04:25,810
He's one crafty old fox...

51
00:04:25,810 --> 00:04:28,310
Every year he just goes overboard...

52
00:04:28,310 --> 00:04:31,640
And of course, the person who comes in last

53
00:04:31,640 --> 00:04:35,180
will face a punishment of which there 
is nothing scarier on the planet!

54
00:04:37,010 --> 00:04:41,150
Isn't this all because the master looks 
forward to giving out the punishment?

55
00:04:41,150 --> 00:04:43,060
Last year was just awful...

56
00:04:43,060 --> 00:04:45,670
It's only one person, though.

57
00:04:45,670 --> 00:04:48,650
As long as you don't come 
in last, what's the problem?

58
00:04:48,650 --> 00:04:51,460
That is a quite logical way of thinking.

59
00:04:51,460 --> 00:04:53,410
But it is far too negative!

60
00:04:53,630 --> 00:04:54,640
Oh, yeah?

61
00:04:55,110 --> 00:04:57,690
I compete only to win.

62
00:04:59,930 --> 00:05:02,560
This is a special outfit that 
reduces my muscle fatigue,

63
00:05:02,560 --> 00:05:05,420
allowing me to run continuously 
for a long time.

64
00:05:05,830 --> 00:05:08,070
She's really going for the win...

65
00:05:08,700 --> 00:05:11,780
Happy. Today only, we're rivals.

66
00:05:11,780 --> 00:05:13,400
I ain't gonna go easy on you.

67
00:05:13,400 --> 00:05:14,700
I know!

68
00:05:14,700 --> 00:05:15,670
But...

69
00:05:15,670 --> 00:05:18,210
This new rule sucks big time.

70
00:05:18,210 --> 00:05:19,580
D-Dark!

71
00:05:19,850 --> 00:05:22,900
Now... It's finally time for the start!

72
00:05:22,900 --> 00:05:25,430
Everyone, to the start line!

73
00:05:27,250 --> 00:05:29,630
Levy, watch my start!

74
00:05:29,630 --> 00:05:31,430
I don't have time for that!

75
00:05:32,050 --> 00:05:33,970
He just wants to show you how cool he is.

76
00:05:33,970 --> 00:05:38,560
You probably don't realize, Lu-chan, but I 
couldn't watch him at the start if I wanted to.

77
00:05:43,080 --> 00:05:44,730
Ready!

78
00:05:45,300 --> 00:05:45,940
Bam!

79
00:05:47,740 --> 00:05:49,380
Here I go!

80
00:05:49,380 --> 00:05:51,160
High Speed!

81
00:05:51,160 --> 00:05:55,000
Pulling away right at the 
start is Jet again this year!

82
00:05:58,160 --> 00:06:00,660
Couldn't see him, right?

83
00:06:00,660 --> 00:06:02,450
No kidding...

84
00:06:06,190 --> 00:06:07,740
Seriously?!

85
00:06:07,740 --> 00:06:10,100
Check out my secret weapon!

86
00:06:10,100 --> 00:06:12,100
It's Fists of the Fire Dragon boosters!

87
00:06:12,100 --> 00:06:16,100
Jet, Natsu! That's totally not right!

88
00:06:16,100 --> 00:06:19,680
Lucy-san, Levy-san, if you'll pardon us!

89
00:06:19,910 --> 00:06:21,950
Today, everyone is our enemy.

90
00:06:21,950 --> 00:06:24,480
You really don't have to be so polite.

91
00:06:24,480 --> 00:06:25,470
Crap!

92
00:06:25,470 --> 00:06:27,470
We're the last ones!

93
00:06:27,470 --> 00:06:30,950
Now then, who'll be getting the punishment?

94
00:06:30,950 --> 00:06:33,810
I can't wait!

95
00:06:40,450 --> 00:06:41,480
Sorry, Happy!

96
00:06:41,480 --> 00:06:42,190
See ya!

97
00:06:45,110 --> 00:06:48,220
Jet's already running off by himself!

98
00:06:48,220 --> 00:06:49,590
And behind him, Natsu!

99
00:06:49,590 --> 00:06:54,110
The idea of using his Fists of the Fire 
Dragon as boosters is totally cool!

100
00:06:54,110 --> 00:06:59,030
Then there's Erza and Gajeel 
leading a huge pack!

101
00:06:59,030 --> 00:07:02,100
Who will it be that makes a break for it?

102
00:07:02,100 --> 00:07:06,530
Let's hear from our expert 
commentator, Mirajane!

103
00:07:06,850 --> 00:07:08,600
Jet's so fast...

104
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:10,570
...we can't film him.

105
00:07:17,500 --> 00:07:19,180
Pict Magic!

106
00:07:23,100 --> 00:07:24,840
What a cinch!

107
00:07:24,840 --> 00:07:26,500
Everyone, fall!

108
00:07:29,600 --> 00:07:32,310
That's what you get for 
layin' back and paintin'!

109
00:07:32,710 --> 00:07:35,480
Ice Make Floor!

110
00:07:41,400 --> 00:07:43,170
All's fair!

111
00:07:43,170 --> 00:07:45,230
Gray, you bastard!

112
00:07:45,230 --> 00:07:46,980
Beast Arm...

113
00:07:49,690 --> 00:07:51,460
Iron Bull!

114
00:07:52,620 --> 00:07:53,940
Gray-sama?

115
00:07:57,630 --> 00:07:59,010
This is tough work...

116
00:07:59,010 --> 00:08:00,750
You drink too much, Cana!

117
00:08:00,750 --> 00:08:02,900
You look just as tired as me, Wakaba!

118
00:08:02,900 --> 00:08:05,750
I didn't think I'd gotten this out of shape!

119
00:08:05,750 --> 00:08:08,440
Can we even make it to the goal?

120
00:08:08,770 --> 00:08:10,580
You guys are pitiful.

121
00:08:10,970 --> 00:08:14,620
Learn from this, and lay off 
the booze and tobacco a little.

122
00:08:19,080 --> 00:08:20,200
What is this?

123
00:08:20,200 --> 00:08:21,470
Runes?

124
00:08:21,470 --> 00:08:22,850
Is it Freed?

125
00:08:22,850 --> 00:08:24,960
He's booby-trapped the course!

126
00:08:24,960 --> 00:08:26,480
Exactly.

127
00:08:26,750 --> 00:08:28,730
Are you never going to let us out?

128
00:08:28,730 --> 00:08:33,050
I know he said anything other than flying 
magic is allowed, but this goes too far!

129
00:08:33,050 --> 00:08:35,140
I never said you couldn't go free.

130
00:08:40,250 --> 00:08:41,660
What are these?

131
00:08:41,660 --> 00:08:45,730
"Practice Questions for the Magic 
Four-Wheeler License Exam"?

132
00:08:45,730 --> 00:08:49,600
This one's "Practice Questions for the Level 
3 Four Elements Sorcerer Qualification"?

133
00:08:49,600 --> 00:08:51,800
Freed, what's the meaning of this?

134
00:08:51,800 --> 00:08:57,340
To escape from these runes, you must answer 
all the questions, and get them all correct.

135
00:08:57,590 --> 00:08:59,270
What?!

136
00:08:59,270 --> 00:09:03,810
If this race purports to test both 
physical and mental strength,

137
00:09:03,810 --> 00:09:07,560
then this little side game is 
entertaining as well as fitting.

138
00:09:07,560 --> 00:09:10,780
If you feel bitter, blame yourselves 
for falling into my trap.

139
00:09:12,090 --> 00:09:13,740
Hold it, Freed!

140
00:09:13,740 --> 00:09:15,480
Blame ourselves?

141
00:09:15,480 --> 00:09:18,190
It was <i>you</i> who activated the runes...

142
00:09:18,190 --> 00:09:20,610
<i>We</i> were just caught up in it!

143
00:09:20,610 --> 00:09:21,570
We've got no choice!

144
00:09:21,570 --> 00:09:22,940
We'll solve all the problems!

145
00:09:22,940 --> 00:09:25,010
Do them yourself!

146
00:09:25,010 --> 00:09:26,580
Forgive me, friends!

147
00:09:25,010 --> 00:09:27,300
You meanies!

148
00:09:29,100 --> 00:09:31,600
She is brave for not using magic.

149
00:09:33,960 --> 00:09:35,330
Runes?

150
00:09:35,330 --> 00:09:36,430
Titania!

151
00:09:36,830 --> 00:09:39,080
Your senses are as perceptive as ever!

152
00:09:39,080 --> 00:09:42,470
You may have noticed the 
rune trap, however...

153
00:09:45,470 --> 00:09:48,540
Breaking my running rhythm 
is a serious offense.

154
00:09:48,540 --> 00:09:50,660
Now I have to get my rhythm back...

155
00:09:50,660 --> 00:09:52,070
Erza, let me out of here!

156
00:09:52,070 --> 00:09:53,400
Hey!

157
00:09:54,030 --> 00:09:58,310
After getting past his tricks, 
she zings one back at him!

158
00:09:58,310 --> 00:10:01,450
The race has gotten completely unpredictable!

159
00:10:01,450 --> 00:10:03,690
No one wants to face the punishment.

160
00:10:04,350 --> 00:10:05,200
Oh?

161
00:10:05,690 --> 00:10:08,570
There's movement near the top of Mt. Ivor!

162
00:10:09,140 --> 00:10:10,480
Could it be?

163
00:10:11,830 --> 00:10:13,950
It's Jet!

164
00:10:13,950 --> 00:10:18,150
The pre-race speculation was right on the 
money, as Jet is the first to reach the summit!

165
00:10:20,960 --> 00:10:22,770
He took a Wyvern scale!

166
00:10:22,770 --> 00:10:25,100
Now all he has to do is come back!

167
00:10:25,520 --> 00:10:28,620
Jet's speed isn't waning in the slightest!

168
00:10:28,620 --> 00:10:31,030
Who will get there next?!

169
00:10:31,030 --> 00:10:32,780
Ah, I'm beat...

170
00:10:32,780 --> 00:10:35,250
I can't go on anymore. I need a little break.

171
00:10:35,250 --> 00:10:37,350
Lu-chan, you have to keep going!

172
00:10:37,350 --> 00:10:39,650
But my legs won't move!

173
00:10:39,650 --> 00:10:42,720
Levy-chan, you go ahead. I'll catch up.

174
00:10:42,720 --> 00:10:43,740
Okay.

175
00:10:43,740 --> 00:10:45,740
I'll be going now.

176
00:10:46,620 --> 00:10:48,550
My legs hurt...

177
00:10:48,550 --> 00:10:50,500
Is there anything I can make use of?

178
00:10:50,750 --> 00:10:53,210
Anyone good to rely on at a time like this...

179
00:10:54,450 --> 00:10:56,550
Gate of the Maiden, I open thee!

180
00:10:56,810 --> 00:10:57,870
Virgo!

181
00:11:00,970 --> 00:11:03,070
You called, Princess?

182
00:11:03,070 --> 00:11:05,440
Carry me up to the peak!

183
00:11:05,440 --> 00:11:07,100
And do it on the double!

184
00:11:07,100 --> 00:11:08,220
As you wish.

185
00:11:09,590 --> 00:11:10,700
This'll be a breeze!

186
00:11:10,700 --> 00:11:12,500
Full speed ahead!

187
00:11:12,500 --> 00:11:13,560
I depart!

188
00:11:16,250 --> 00:11:17,320
Lu-chan?

189
00:11:18,440 --> 00:11:19,610
I'm gonna fall! I'm gonna fall!

190
00:11:19,610 --> 00:11:21,900
Let me down, I'm scared!

191
00:11:25,460 --> 00:11:27,590
What lovely water...

192
00:11:27,590 --> 00:11:29,900
The fatigue is washing right away...

193
00:11:30,450 --> 00:11:32,510
Ah, Gray-sama...

194
00:11:32,510 --> 00:11:34,460
Sorry for earlier.

195
00:11:36,730 --> 00:11:43,550
Juvia was also scared of this "punishment", so 
she didn't help you, and instead went on ahead!

196
00:11:44,150 --> 00:11:47,710
But Juvia is tormented by what she did!

197
00:11:47,710 --> 00:11:53,900
Until Gray-sama comes to this place, Juvia 
will rest herself in this cool water...

198
00:11:53,900 --> 00:11:55,480
Like this...

199
00:12:07,160 --> 00:12:09,440
Was that... Juvia-san?

200
00:12:09,440 --> 00:12:11,450
Ah, the water-user.

201
00:12:11,450 --> 00:12:17,180
While she was soaking in the water, she must 
have changed herself to water by accident.

202
00:12:19,150 --> 00:12:21,380
Have you seen Juvia around here?

203
00:12:22,210 --> 00:12:23,130
Seriously?

204
00:12:23,820 --> 00:12:27,230
Gray-sama!

205
00:12:29,830 --> 00:12:32,090
Go, go, go!

206
00:12:32,660 --> 00:12:34,890
Whoa there, they stopped!

207
00:12:37,580 --> 00:12:39,110
Out of fuel?

208
00:12:41,360 --> 00:12:43,830
Well, I was going full-power all this time.

209
00:12:45,120 --> 00:12:46,090
Gajeel!

210
00:12:46,090 --> 00:12:47,900
Outta my way!

211
00:12:53,070 --> 00:12:55,370
Gajeel, you bastard!

212
00:12:59,100 --> 00:13:01,600
Can I eat that fire?

213
00:13:08,500 --> 00:13:10,660
It's been 12 hours since the start!

214
00:13:10,660 --> 00:13:13,270
The moon has already 
risen over the night sky!

215
00:13:13,520 --> 00:13:17,100
Right now, the wizards are taking 
Wyvern scales one after another

216
00:13:17,100 --> 00:13:20,520
and blasting on to the return course!

217
00:13:30,600 --> 00:13:32,330
Finally, here...

218
00:13:58,020 --> 00:13:59,380
Oh, Happy!

219
00:13:59,380 --> 00:14:00,690
Natsu!

220
00:14:06,050 --> 00:14:07,770
Thanks, Natsu!

221
00:14:09,010 --> 00:14:10,230
I'm taking off.

222
00:14:10,500 --> 00:14:12,240
Don't slack off on the way!

223
00:14:12,240 --> 00:14:13,430
I know!

224
00:14:13,430 --> 00:14:14,940
Fists of the Fire Dragon!

225
00:14:18,490 --> 00:14:21,520
The 24 Hours Endurance Road Race!

226
00:14:21,520 --> 00:14:24,480
We're well into the second half! Cool!

227
00:14:24,710 --> 00:14:27,430
All the wizards, with Wyvern scale in hand,

228
00:14:27,430 --> 00:14:33,310
are racing full speed toward 
the Magnolia South Gate Park!

229
00:14:33,310 --> 00:14:35,470
Still in the lead is Jet, as always!

230
00:14:35,470 --> 00:14:40,170
Next up is Erza, who 
doesn't even look winded!

231
00:14:40,170 --> 00:14:44,760
The next group is Gray, Lucy, and 
Gajeel, who are still running strong!

232
00:14:44,760 --> 00:14:46,360
Cool!

233
00:14:46,360 --> 00:14:51,330
Behind them is the full pack in pursuit, 
not losing focus for an instant!

234
00:14:51,330 --> 00:14:53,400
Who will be coming in last?

235
00:14:53,400 --> 00:14:56,100
Who will be receiving the 
punishment this year?

236
00:14:56,100 --> 00:14:58,690
You can't miss a second!

237
00:15:02,160 --> 00:15:03,870
Bunch of slackers...

238
00:15:03,870 --> 00:15:06,270
Let's liven things up a bit.

239
00:15:17,340 --> 00:15:19,370
Cool!

240
00:15:19,370 --> 00:15:21,090
The race has entered the final stage!

241
00:15:21,090 --> 00:15:24,540
The super-high-speed Jet is so fast, 
we've completely lost sight of him!

242
00:15:27,200 --> 00:15:28,950
But!

243
00:15:28,950 --> 00:15:31,840
Natsu and the rest are 
gutsily gaining ground!

244
00:15:31,840 --> 00:15:33,780
Cool!

245
00:15:34,040 --> 00:15:36,700
Everyone has worked hard through the night.

246
00:15:37,140 --> 00:15:44,390
We had better switch to our seats at South 
Gate Park, and get ready to watch the finish!

247
00:15:46,920 --> 00:15:48,010
Huh?

248
00:15:48,650 --> 00:15:50,130
Jet?

249
00:15:50,440 --> 00:15:51,870
Are you asleep?

250
00:15:51,870 --> 00:15:53,780
Hey, Jet!

251
00:15:53,780 --> 00:15:55,920
Wake up, Jet!

252
00:15:57,810 --> 00:15:59,220
Hey, Happy.

253
00:15:59,220 --> 00:16:01,650
Should you be sleeping now?

254
00:16:04,290 --> 00:16:06,070
I overslept!

255
00:16:06,070 --> 00:16:08,110
Everyone's gone ahead.

256
00:16:08,110 --> 00:16:09,740
Thanks, Happy.

257
00:16:09,740 --> 00:16:11,320
I gotta make up for lost time!

258
00:16:13,900 --> 00:16:16,290
It's the last spurt toward the goal!

259
00:16:16,290 --> 00:16:18,470
The battle for second is heating up!

260
00:16:18,470 --> 00:16:21,180
All right! We can see Magnolia!

261
00:16:22,470 --> 00:16:23,410
What?

262
00:16:23,670 --> 00:16:25,370
Oh, what's this?

263
00:16:26,290 --> 00:16:27,210
Jet?

264
00:16:27,830 --> 00:16:29,770
What? He wasn't in the lead?

265
00:16:33,200 --> 00:16:35,770
Why is Jet behind us?

266
00:16:35,770 --> 00:16:39,640
Wait, then that means we're 
in contention to win?!

267
00:16:39,640 --> 00:16:40,640
Why?!

268
00:16:40,640 --> 00:16:43,270
Jet is catching up as fast as he can!

269
00:16:44,680 --> 00:16:47,300
So fast! Passing them in a flash!

270
00:16:48,250 --> 00:16:49,670
I don't think so!

271
00:16:49,670 --> 00:16:50,740
Requip!

272
00:16:52,940 --> 00:16:54,470
A rabbit?

273
00:16:54,470 --> 00:16:57,210
Is this your trump card for the last spurt?

274
00:16:59,710 --> 00:17:00,740
Huh?

275
00:17:00,740 --> 00:17:02,080
She's not catching up...

276
00:17:02,080 --> 00:17:04,230
That's actually really slow for a rabbit.

277
00:17:04,230 --> 00:17:05,960
She must've bought it based 
on the way it looked!

278
00:17:05,960 --> 00:17:09,500
Maybe she's more about appearances?

279
00:17:09,500 --> 00:17:12,150
Hold it, you guys!

280
00:17:17,130 --> 00:17:21,020
Now in Magnolia, Jet's finally neck and neck!

281
00:17:21,020 --> 00:17:24,020
The winner has been narrowed 
down to one of these 5!

282
00:17:24,290 --> 00:17:25,350
Fists of the Fire Dragon!

283
00:17:25,350 --> 00:17:26,850
As if!

284
00:17:27,480 --> 00:17:28,520
Requip!

285
00:17:35,260 --> 00:17:37,490
Natsu's fists are out of fuel!

286
00:17:37,490 --> 00:17:39,280
Is he out of contention to win?

287
00:17:39,540 --> 00:17:43,120
It's not over yet!

288
00:17:43,120 --> 00:17:45,420
Yeah! Never count Natsu out!

289
00:17:45,420 --> 00:17:48,070
He's digging deep into 
top groove to close in!

290
00:17:48,070 --> 00:17:50,270
I won't lose!

291
00:17:59,000 --> 00:18:02,220
I won't lose!

292
00:18:03,980 --> 00:18:06,930
Victory is mine!

293
00:18:15,450 --> 00:18:18,000
There's a huge crash!

294
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:21,630
Wait, who's that cool cat coming up?

295
00:18:21,630 --> 00:18:22,840
It's Happy!

296
00:18:22,840 --> 00:18:24,900
Happy is here!

297
00:18:24,900 --> 00:18:26,080
Happy?

298
00:18:27,580 --> 00:18:30,900
Yes, the goal is right ahead!

299
00:18:36,130 --> 00:18:37,840
All right!

300
00:18:37,840 --> 00:18:39,740
I won!

301
00:18:39,740 --> 00:18:41,830
Congratulations, Happy!

302
00:18:41,830 --> 00:18:44,400
Yes! You ran well!

303
00:18:44,400 --> 00:18:45,980
Aye!

304
00:18:46,550 --> 00:18:52,380
Goal! Happy is the winner of this 
year's 24 Hours Endurance Road Race!

305
00:18:52,380 --> 00:18:56,570
History has been made! Nothing 
will ever be the same, folks!

306
00:18:56,570 --> 00:19:00,380
Cool! Cool! Cool!

307
00:19:00,840 --> 00:19:03,220
I did it!

308
00:19:03,220 --> 00:19:04,420
You've got to be kidding me.

309
00:19:04,420 --> 00:19:05,970
He got us.

310
00:19:05,970 --> 00:19:07,660
The cat?

311
00:19:09,200 --> 00:19:11,590
Not a bad ending, I say.

312
00:19:11,590 --> 00:19:13,880
He woke me up.

313
00:19:13,880 --> 00:19:17,230
Ah well, I'll let him win this time.

314
00:19:19,070 --> 00:19:20,060
Wendy?!

315
00:19:20,060 --> 00:19:21,170
Carla?!

316
00:19:21,750 --> 00:19:23,330
Whoa there!

317
00:19:23,330 --> 00:19:26,210
Coming in second is Wendy, 
and third is Carla!

318
00:19:26,210 --> 00:19:30,850
The top three spots are occupied 
by these three Fairy Tail pretties!

319
00:19:33,200 --> 00:19:34,220
What?

320
00:19:34,220 --> 00:19:35,660
This is...

321
00:19:35,660 --> 00:19:39,150
No one wants to face the punishment!

322
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:43,600
Don't step on me!

323
00:19:44,800 --> 00:19:47,550
What's this?!

324
00:19:47,550 --> 00:19:51,850
A battalion of wizards all 
crossed the goal at once!

325
00:19:51,850 --> 00:19:54,270
Quick thinking Erza also crossed the goal.

326
00:19:55,210 --> 00:19:56,940
Gray-sama, hurry!

327
00:19:56,940 --> 00:19:58,090
Natsu!

328
00:19:58,090 --> 00:19:59,930
Everyone, hurry!

329
00:19:59,930 --> 00:20:00,960
Shoot!

330
00:20:00,960 --> 00:20:02,170
Crap!

331
00:20:02,170 --> 00:20:04,870
Easy for you to say!

332
00:20:04,870 --> 00:20:07,630
This ain't no joke! High Speed!

333
00:20:07,910 --> 00:20:08,680
What?

334
00:20:08,680 --> 00:20:10,350
Jet!

335
00:20:10,350 --> 00:20:12,960
Go-go-go-goal!

336
00:20:12,960 --> 00:20:15,400
The 4 of you crossed at the same time!

337
00:20:15,400 --> 00:20:17,010
What?!

338
00:20:17,010 --> 00:20:19,190
This year was whacked out!

339
00:20:19,190 --> 00:20:22,490
This finish was cooler than cool!

340
00:20:22,490 --> 00:20:27,810
Coming in last was, incredibly, 
Natsu, Gajeel, Gray, and Jet!

341
00:20:27,810 --> 00:20:30,310
We know who'll get punished!

342
00:20:31,650 --> 00:20:33,790
Are you prepared?

343
00:20:33,790 --> 00:20:35,430
You're kidding, right, Gramps?

344
00:20:35,430 --> 00:20:38,950
Gramps! At least let us have a tie-breaker!

345
00:20:38,950 --> 00:20:40,570
No!

346
00:20:40,570 --> 00:20:42,550
I won't hear any more 
of your pitiful excuses!

347
00:20:42,550 --> 00:20:48,130
For a wizard, there are no 
do-overs, for jobs or otherwise!

348
00:20:48,130 --> 00:20:51,920
Stop acting like babies 
and take your punishment!

349
00:20:51,920 --> 00:20:53,270
All four of you!

350
00:20:54,600 --> 00:20:56,540
Fine, I got it!

351
00:20:56,540 --> 00:20:58,380
I'll do whatever!

352
00:20:58,380 --> 00:21:00,270
Tell us what the punishment is.

353
00:21:00,270 --> 00:21:02,350
There! That's the spirit.

354
00:21:02,350 --> 00:21:05,520
I will now announce this year's punishment!

355
00:21:05,520 --> 00:21:07,600
Right here!

356
00:21:08,050 --> 00:21:10,040
Weekly Sorcerer?

357
00:21:10,040 --> 00:21:11,810
What about it?

358
00:21:11,810 --> 00:21:19,500
The four of you will do a super-embarrassing 
photo spread for the issue two weeks from now!

359
00:21:19,500 --> 00:21:24,310
A super-magnificent 20 pages, together 
with a one-week, all-access interview!

360
00:21:27,000 --> 00:21:29,750
A super-embarrassing photo spread?

361
00:21:30,020 --> 00:21:34,540
I'll go buy a display and 
preservation tools, Gray-sama!

362
00:21:34,540 --> 00:21:35,930
Don't do that!

363
00:21:35,930 --> 00:21:40,680
Now then, everyone... Let's go right 
ahead and start picking out clothes!

364
00:21:43,650 --> 00:21:45,050
Wait!

365
00:21:45,050 --> 00:21:46,830
Oh, hell no!

366
00:21:46,830 --> 00:21:48,700
Wait! Cool!

367
00:21:48,700 --> 00:21:50,670
They're running again?

368
00:21:50,670 --> 00:21:53,000
Seems they still have plenty of stamina.

369
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:54,180
As expected.

370
00:21:54,180 --> 00:21:55,890
I don't think that's what it is.

371
00:21:55,890 --> 00:21:58,250
Gray-sama's photo spread!

372
00:21:58,560 --> 00:22:00,400
By the way, Master...

373
00:22:00,840 --> 00:22:04,900
I won, so do I get something nice?

374
00:22:04,900 --> 00:22:06,720
You already did!

375
00:22:09,660 --> 00:22:12,580
You got the joy of winning 
and everyone's cheers!

376
00:22:12,580 --> 00:22:15,100
There is no greater honor, am I right?

377
00:22:15,370 --> 00:22:17,720
Wait, seriously?

378
00:22:17,720 --> 00:22:19,420
That's it?

379
00:22:19,420 --> 00:22:21,180
Seriously...?

380
00:22:21,450 --> 00:22:23,690
Aww...

381
00:23:55,620 --> 00:23:58,260
Gildarts has finally come back?!

382
00:23:58,260 --> 00:24:02,740
Aye! He's been away on a quest 
for who knows how many years.

383
00:24:02,740 --> 00:24:04,450
I can't wait to meet him!

384
00:24:04,450 --> 00:24:05,370
Yeah!

385
00:24:05,370 --> 00:24:07,270
When he gets back, I'm 
challenging him right away!

386
00:24:07,270 --> 00:24:08,840
Even though you'll just lose?

387
00:24:08,840 --> 00:24:10,040
I'll win this time.

388
00:24:10,040 --> 00:24:11,430
Definitely win!

389
00:24:11,430 --> 00:24:13,900
Have you <i>ever</i> won after saying that?

390
00:24:14,250 --> 00:24:16,510
Next time: Gildarts.

391
00:24:16,900 --> 00:24:19,670
Happy, prepare a party to 
celebrate my first victory!

392
00:24:19,670 --> 00:24:20,100
Aye!

393
00:24:20,100 --> 00:24:22,410
I'll prepare for a "better 
luck next time" party!

394
00:24:22,410 --> 00:24:24,640
Were you even listening to me?!

